but be concerned about
the long-term effects

252
00:08:51,180 --> 00:08:52,800
of living under these conditions.

253
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:55,680
In my youth, I thought
I was invincible, too.

254
00:08:55,680 --> 00:08:57,720
And after working myself to the bone,

255
00:08:57,720 --> 00:08:59,220
I had a serious health scare

256
00:08:59,220 --> 00:09:01,140
that shocked me back to reality.

257
00:09:01,140 --> 00:09:04,113
I wonder if Iman is heading
down a similar path.

258
00:09:04,950 --> 00:09:06,480
- I'd never called myself British, though.

259
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:08,160
- No?
- Nah.

260
00:09:08,160 --> 00:09:09,240
- So what'd you call yourself?

261
00:09:09,240 --> 00:09:11,254
- Confused.
- Confused!

262
00:09:11,254 --> 00:09:15,480
Before I knew it, we'd arrived
at our next destination:

263
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:16,706
The desert.

264
00:09:16,706 --> 00:09:17,827
(intense upbeat music)

265
00:09:17,827 --> 00:09:21,432
♪ You seem to know something I don't ♪

266
00:09:21,432 --> 00:09:25,224
♪ What's going on, can you
tell me what it is, please ♪

267
00:09:25,224 --> 00:09:28,804
♪ I'm not that slow, like you think ♪

268
00:09:28,804 --> 00:09:33,804
♪ Strange vibrations in the
room and I can feel it ♪

269
00:09:35,705 --> 00:09:37,920
- He already knows he's screwed.

270
00:09:37,920 --> 00:09:39,150
- Got it.

271
00:09:39,150 --> 00:09:41,010
I'll tell you what, it's
hurting my hip, actually.

272
00:09:41,010 --> 00:09:41,970
I've gotta be honest.

273
00:09:41,970 --> 00:09:44,051
It's a pretty wide animal.

274
00:09:44,051 --> 00:09:47,190
I thought it was meant to
be a camel, not an elephant.

275
00:09:47,190 --> 00:09:48,420
I'm slightly scared.

276
00:09:48,420 --> 00:09:50,074
Here we go.

277
00:09:50,074 --> 00:09:50,907
Oh!

278
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:54,180
Oh, that's high up.

279
00:09:54,180 --> 00:09:55,320
Unbelievable.

280
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:57,240
Look at my eyelashes on my camel.

281
00:09:57,240 --> 00:10:00,929
That's gotta be one of the
prettiest camels in existence.

282
00:10:00,929 --> 00:10:04,476
♪ I'm a hurricane, I'm
bringing thunder and rain ♪

283
00:10:04,476 --> 00:10:09,393
♪ I'm a hurricane if you get in my way ♪

284
00:10:09,393 --> 00:10:12,360
Big downhill section coming up.

285
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:13,193
Cheese!

286
00:10:14,031 --> 00:10:16,698
(upbeat music)

287
00:10:18,305 --> 00:10:19,583
That's a ride, just getting off!

288
00:10:20,741 --> 00:10:23,408
(pensive music)

289
00:10:24,690 --> 00:10:28,590
Middle of the desert and
we got a classy restaurant.

290
00:10:28,590 --> 00:10:30,450
You said that you didn't want to ever

291
00:10:30,450 --> 00:10:33,900
become a billionaire because
of the responsibility

292
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:36,210
that goes with it and
the control from above.

293
00:10:36,210 --> 00:10:38,220
- I don't wanna be
viewed as a billionaire.

294
00:10:38,220 --> 00:10:39,659
- [Interviewer] That's a big difference.

295
00:10:39,659 --> 00:10:42,270
- Let's say, for example,
in Middle Eastern families

296
00:10:42,270 --> 00:10:45,480
like you put like the top
10 richest people on earth.

297
00:10:45,480 --> 00:10:47,760
Combine them all times five.

298
00:10:47,760 --> 00:10:50,100
They're still not as rich as the Qataris,

299
00:10:50,100 --> 00:10:51,270
but you're not gonna find the Qataris

300
00:10:51,270 --> 00:10:53,400
on the world's rich list, you know?

301
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:56,040
So like people don't know
where the real actual money is.

302
00:10:56,040 --> 00:10:59,130
- Do you ever feel like you've lived three

303
00:10:59,130 --> 00:11:02,550
or four lives already in your 23 years?

304
00:11:02,550 --> 00:11:04,350
- Yeah, it doesn't feel like
my first life, that's for sure.

305
00:11:04,350 --> 00:11:07,236
I'm a little jaded 'cause
I've experienced a lot.

306
00:11:07,236 --> 00:11:09,903
(upbeat music)

307
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:16,830
- After an amazing couple of hours,

308
00:11:16,830 --> 00:11:20,220
I began thinking this is
probably just a normal day

309
00:11:20,220 --> 00:11:23,340
for Iman and if I did all
these things at his age,

310
00:11:23,340 --> 00:11:25,200
what would there be to look forward to?

311
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:27,990
When I became a millionaire
in my early twenties,

312
00:11:27,990 --> 00:11:30,270
I was very cautious of
letting my lifestyle

313
00:11:30,270 --> 00:11:31,380
get outta control.

314
00:11:31,380 --> 00:11:34,290
I know it sounds funny,
but I had this rule

315
00:11:34,290 --> 00:11:36,420
that I would do something
that made my life

316
00:11:36,420 --> 00:11:40,350
a bit better each year, but
Iman's already done it all.

317
00:11:40,350 --> 00:11:42,900
So I was curious to see
how he approached this

318
00:11:42,900 --> 00:11:44,301
potential issue.

319
00:11:44,301 --> 00:11:48,330
You ever worry when you can
see all the experiences,

320
00:11:48,330 --> 00:11:49,718
do all the experiences,

321
00:11:49,718 --> 00:11:52,020
that you'll eventually have experienced

322
00:11:52,020 --> 00:11:53,430
everything there is to experience?

323
00:11:53,430 --> 00:11:55,740
- You find what you like
and what you don't like.

324
00:11:55,740 --> 00:11:58,410
Like I couldn't care
less about certain things

325
00:11:58,410 --> 00:11:59,642
that people find-

326
00:11:59,642 --> 00:12:00,802
Like for example, I went on a safari.

327
00:12:00,802 --> 00:12:04,568
Super nice, like a hundred
thousand dollars Safari.

328
00:12:04,568 --> 00:12:06,360
Hated it.
- Really?

329
00:12:06,360 --> 00:12:07,875
- Couldn't care less.

330
00:12:07,875 --> 00:12:09,743
There's only so many times you
can watch a Lion Lick itself.

331
00:12:10,639 --> 00:12:13,680
But I know for some
people that's like insane,

332
00:12:13,680 --> 00:12:14,640
like life-changing.

333
00:12:14,640 --> 00:12:17,880
Compare that and then I had one
night in Nepal where I slept

334
00:12:17,880 --> 00:12:18,713
in a tent.

335
00:12:18,713 --> 00:12:20,970
That was one of my best
memories so far this year.

336
00:12:20,970 --> 00:12:21,803
Like sleeping in a tent.

337
00:12:21,803 --> 00:12:23,490
Certain things you can't explain.

338
00:12:23,490 --> 00:12:24,690
You know, there's just little quirks

339
00:12:24,690 --> 00:12:26,340
and little things that
you just enjoy doing.

340
00:12:26,340 --> 00:12:28,450
Like I just really like
for example, walking.

341
00:12:28,450 --> 00:12:29,910
Rather than a hundred
thousand dollars safari,

342
00:12:29,910 --> 00:12:33,060
I'd rather just walk

343
00:12:33,060 --> 00:12:35,430
in Paris.

344
00:12:35,430 --> 00:12:36,630
- Our day wasn't over yet.

345
00:12:36,630 --> 00:12:40,320
What Iman showed me next
was utterly jaw dropping.

346
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:41,703
Before we open it,

347
00:12:44,430 --> 00:12:47,190
what's the value on
that box I just lifted?

348
00:12:47,190 --> 00:12:48,872
- I dunno, maybe 2?

349
00:12:48,872 --> 00:12:49,705
- Yeah, let's clarify that.

350
00:12:49,705 --> 00:12:51,210
That's 2 million.
- Yeah.

351
00:12:51,210 --> 00:12:53,160
- Pounds?
- Pounds, yeah.

352
00:12:53,160 --> 00:12:55,500
- Two and a half million dollars there.

353
00:12:55,500 --> 00:12:56,895
Oh wow.

354
00:12:56,895 --> 00:12:58,740
Look at that.

355
00:12:58,740 --> 00:13:01,292
Every one's a masterpiece, isn't it?

356
00:13:01,292 --> 00:13:02,376
- I've said publicly,

357
00:13:02,376 --> 00:13:03,570
and I think some people flame me for it,

358
00:13:03,570 --> 00:13:06,090
I said if you have 30,000
pounds in the bank,

359
00:13:06,090 --> 00:13:08,460
why not spend 10 on a watch?

360
00:13:08,460 --> 00:13:11,760
You know, for me it's like
they're easily liquid.

361
00:13:11,760 --> 00:13:13,500
Buy and sell as you please,

362
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:15,360
and you're not really
gonna lose any money.

363
00:13:15,360 --> 00:13:18,060
(upbeat music)

364
00:13:18,060 --> 00:13:19,440
- That's marvelous, that.

365
00:13:19,440 --> 00:13:22,740
I look at that and it's
an amazing collection.

366
00:13:22,740 --> 00:13:23,876
- Thank you, bro.

367
00:13:23,876 --> 00:13:24,750
- You should be really proud of all that.

368
00:13:24,750 --> 00:13:26,080
So let's get down to it.

369
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:29,250
Does Iman have a superiority complex?

370
00:13:29,250 --> 00:13:34,250
Yes, but this has allowed dream
big and achieve greatness.

371
00:13:34,680 --> 00:13:36,720
If you don't think you
are destined for more

372
00:13:36,720 --> 00:13:40,140
than the masses, how are
you ever gonna join the 1%?

373
00:13:40,140 --> 00:13:41,700
He treated me to a lovely day

374
00:13:41,700 --> 00:13:43,440
and gave me some thoughtful gifts.

375
00:13:43,440 --> 00:13:45,690
But are his intentions pure?

376
00:13:45,690 --> 00:13:47,528
After spending more time with him,

377
00:13:47,528 --> 00:13:49,410
I think so.

378
00:13:49,410 --> 00:13:51,690
After living a day in Iman's world,

379
00:13:51,690 --> 00:13:54,390
I was concerned that he'll
have soon experienced all

380
00:13:54,390 --> 00:13:56,310
of life's greatest luxuries.

381
00:13:56,310 --> 00:13:59,705
But it's clear that this
isn't what Iman lives for.

382
00:13:59,705 --> 00:14:03,090
He's more interested in the
simple pleasures of life.

383
00:14:03,090 --> 00:14:05,490
There's lots of responsibility
on his shoulders,

384
00:14:05,490 --> 00:14:07,440
which comes with a lot of stress.

385
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:09,100
Will it get the better of him?

386
00:14:09,100 --> 00:14:11,280
I guess only time will tell.

387
00:14:11,280 --> 00:14:12,629
- Gimme a hug.

388
00:14:12,629 --> 00:14:16,083
Thank you bro.
- Thanks for everything.

